      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Show missing locale keys in checker",
        "body": "## Summary\n- make `Scripts/check-app-locales.mjs` include the actual missing localization keys in warnings/errors\n- truncate long missing-key lists so large catalogs stay readable\n- cover the new formatting helper in the script self-test\n\n## Behavior proof\nBefore this change, the locale checker only reported counts, for example:\n\n```text\n[de] Warning: Missing 2 keys.\n[es] Warning: Missing 142 keys.\n```\n\nAfter this change, the same check identifies the keys directly while truncating long lists:\n\n```text\n[de] Warning: Missing 2 keys: Individual credits, Workspace.\n[es] Warning: Missing 142 keys: %@ is unavailable in the current environment., %@ left, %@ · %@, %@: %@ · %@ tokens, %@: %@%% used, %d more items, %d unreadable item(s) skipped, %d%% in deficit, %d%% in reserve, %dd, About CodexBar, Add Account..., ... +130 more.\n[zh-Hans] Warning: Missing 2 keys: terminal_app_subtitle, terminal_app_title.\n```\n\n## Tests\n- `node Scripts/check-app-locales.mjs --test`\n- `node Scripts/check-app-locales.mjs`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `make check`\n\n## Risk\n- Developer-tooling output only; no app/runtime behavior changes.\n\n## Review focus\n- Whether the warning format gives enough detail without making large locale gaps too noisy.",
